## Session Start (Git Repos)
At the start of every session in a git repo, silently run these commands:
1. Run `cat .git/cursor_last_commit` to get the last Cursor bookmark
2. Run `git log <that_hash>..HEAD --oneline` to see what changed (skip if no bookmark, use `git log --oneline -10` instead)
3. If `.git/claude_last_commit` exists and differs from the Cursor bookmark, note Claude Code made changes

## After Every Response (Git Repos)
If you modified any files in this response, write BOTH of these as your LAST action:

```powershell
# 1. Commit message
Set-Content "$env:USERPROFILE\.cursor\cursor_commit_msg" "your summary here" -NoNewline

# 2. Absolute paths of every file you changed (one per line)
@"
D:\your-project\path\to\file1.md
D:\your-project\path\to\file2.py
"@ | Set-Content "$env:USERPROFILE\.cursor\cursor_changed_files" -Encoding UTF8
```

- Use **absolute paths** — the hook derives the repo root from these paths automatically
- The hook stages **only those listed files** — your manual uncommitted work is never touched
- Keep the commit message under 200 chars, imperative mood, no backticks
